so yeah... cedar pointe trip

not as fun as last year... though there were some better moments

jaimie wasnt there first off.  that pretty much sucked butt.  it was a slow slow start to a comparitavely uneventful trip.  last year was so much more fun.  o man... but yeah.  u were sorely missed jaim.  dani came :)  that was a plus. of course.  the maxair was by far my favorite ride.  it was like being a drunk superman. holy cow that was fun.  lol.  did some little kiddy rides, and died in the heat.  i pretty much sweated all of the water that was in my body.  o man... i hate sweating.  so gross.  no millenium force.  we were too lazy to wait in line.  jerks.  o well... o yeah... i GOT A NEW FREAKING SWEET LAPTOP!! side note there...  i'm using it right now actually.  its sooooo sweet.  anyways.  church tonight... should be fun.  yay! ok... bye!

wow... so both of us get hit hard.  both of us are given a wake up call.  both of us are both put in situations that totally suck.  its like a nightmare that never ends.  u wanna wake up out of it... but nothing happens.  ur just stuck.  stuck in the worst possible scenario.  all you can ask is y?  y God?  why now?  of all times?  just when i'm having the time of my life?  what are u doing?! why are u screwing with my life?  

the thing is though... we both know that God is sovereign.  we both know that everything has a purpose in his perfect plan.  it just sucks to think that all of this bad... is actually for our good in some way.  we cant see it now,  but maybe God's preparing us for something... maybe he's protecting us.  he's waking us up from our childhood and getting us ready for all the real trials and stupidities that are to come.  "i know this hurts... i just hope this may help in the end.  this is the only way i know to help you.  i love you."  that's what he's saying.  "you'll understand in the end" our only job is to listen.  to listen to what he's trying to say, to what he's trying to do.. accept it because there isnt any other thing we can do... and then try to piece together our lives and move on.  

i dk... maybe this helped.  i'm here for you.  i love you, u know that right?

i needed today

an amazing bbq with all my filipino friends.  played nintendo like old times.  laughed, played frisbee.  it was so nice to be with all of them again.  

GOD IS SOOOOOOO AMAZING!!! I LOVE YOU GOD.

-Andrew
God really has his way of waking you up.
so yeah... i was gonna fill out that sweet kissing survey that everyone else did... but i couldnt answer the questions lol...

so i wake up at freaking 7:30 cuz i have to go mow lawns with my bro...  grrr...  good thing the brysons have a sweet trampoline :)  so much fun.  i pretty much jumped on that and called dani since mark was the one the payment check was made out to.  i made him work. bwahahahaha. i wanted to go swimming.. but the gate to the pool was locked.  darn.  mrs thompson drove into the driveway as we pulled out.  too funny.  then drove home to watch kristen as mark and mom went to the dentist.  

we cleaned for a bit cuz dani was coming over :)  we watched hercules, some pbs, and then some homestarrunner to top it all off.  twas amazing.  its been so long since i went on that website... o man.  everything was hilarious.  well at least everything i remember... then dani left and i slept on the couch for a little bit.  i dk what was wrong with me but i was out like a light.  i mean i layed down then the next thing i know we were eating dinner.  ca-razy.  ate like a pig, then went online to go laptop shopping again... sigh.  so annoying.  i wish i could just create my perfect computer, then pay for it right then and there.  anyone wanna give me $2000?  if only...  

pulled some weeds outside, and then updated. 

i wanna go to europe again :(

hung out with ppl a lot... SWEET

college plans?... a bit stressing... but whatever

so... yeah teen week has been prettty...sad.  i dk... its better than last years.  lol.  yesterday we had more than the high day last year...so yeah... kinda sad.  yesterday was so stinking hot.  the games were pointless and my team lost a lot of the time.  but we tied! woo!  yeah....right.

today was a lot better than yesterday.  o man... even though ppl got sick and threw up and jaimie left early, and i got a grasscut... it was still fun.  that brandon kid is pretty cool.  i think he may actually like our church.  weird. lol.  we did some water games... bobbed for apples and marshmallows.. o man.  i got a mouthful of flour.  gross.  everything was like baking onto my face.  good pictures...  we shot balloons at each other (really sad), and spit in buckets.  slid on some tarp.  sweet... played some bball afterwards.  kinda cool.  

alrighty... well dani's leaving for canada tomorrow and jaimie is sick...  :(  i still have all my other friends though :)  right? right?

O!  we saw Jasmine at Big Boy! yes...Jasmine from aladdin... o man... she was really chubby though lol.  i got a dragon tattoo..  it was pretty sweet lol.  ur all jealous

-Andrew

today was pretty fun? i dk lol.  i spent the whole day with dani pretty much :) so that was good.  she picked mark and me up at 9 in the morning so that we could help her hand out flyers for her moms company... she drove, mark folded flyers and i stuck my head out the window and shoved flyers in newspaper boxes.  it was sweet.  my body was half out the door and there was a nice breeze.  dani was embarrassed... but i didnt care lol.  it was pretty fun.  then we ate lunch at wendy's.  mmmmmmm.... good stuff.  did some more flyers, then tried looking for the salvation army up there so that dani could go thrifting for the first time ever.  but we didnt find it and settled for old navy.  didnt get nething cuz i'm broke.  bleh...  o well.  the life of a college man.  then she drove us home and hung out for a bit.  we looked at pictures and watched some pbs lol.  then she went home :(  

i get to see her tomorrow though :)

so today i woke up cuz pastor jeff called.  at first i'm confused and a bit irritated cuz he woke me up...but then i see the clock and discover that its almost 12.  oops.  so i talked to him for a bit.  he's doing good for everyone that cares.  then i was gonna go running in the morning... but it was way too hot outside for that, so i called dani.  talked to her for about an hour.  yay :)  i really missed talking to her.  oh man.  so i've pretty much called her twice a day for the past... 2 days.  its only been 2 days since i've been back?  holy crap time goes by slow.  o well...  then i ate food.  then i took a shower.  and then i worked out for like an hour.  havent done that in a while...so it was pretty nice.  now i'm waiting for jaime g to call... so we can hang out.  bye!
so i got to play some bball today... and cleaned my room.  saw dani and doug and ericka.  that was fun

I'M HOME!!!! WOOOOOOOO!!!!!!!! I LOVE AMERICA!!!! lol... for real though i had a pretty good trip overall.  no flushing toilets...or showers... but i survived.  my family pretty much makes up half the philippines.  bigger than a chaldean family... they all intermarry and stuff too... GROSS!! my relatives were trying to set me up with some of my cousins... they were all like "these are your SECOND cousins..."  AH! i dont wanna be a hillbilly! lol.  i saw a pig get slaughtered.  ate dog.  ate a duck fetus... Ca-Razy!  imported illegal starfish...got some pirated crap... o yes.  good trip. lol.  


so i was kinda stressing about what to do about classes and such for next year.... but i found out today that i know when i get there what classes i'm taking.  sweet.  i'm pretty pumped about the sample classes i saw on the website though.... should be fun!!






so y is it that whenever i leave... things fall apart?

i love pirated DVD's

i can now watch movies that are out right now...before next year!!!

Madagascar
Batman Begins

more to come... bwahahahahahaha

woo!! i'm home!!


i hate michigan


its so freaking cold here!! o my goodness... 

well mexico was fun/insane.  we worked at this new church building in tampico.  its by the gulf of mexico.  we couldnt freaking flush our toilet paper!! and...we didnt have toilet seats until like the 3rd to last day!! and...the shower was a trickle down the wall! gross! huge spiders, roaches, mosquitoes...  

but we did build like 6 cement stairs, made 8 cement pillars, dug 4  2 feet deep holes, and put on a vbs for little children... so fun.  i love little tiny mexicans! lol.  

i want to sleep...so sry for the short entry

pray for me tomorrow! or today... cuz i'll be flying for like 20 freaking hours!!!

-Andrew

wow...so when was the last time i updated?

well lets just update from the last memory in my mind...  

open house was fun...got muchos money/towels? what?  lol yeah... towels and body cleaning stuff... that's awesome! i'll be nice and fresh and clean in college! yeah! hmm.. tuesday... dani came over and we watched peter pan! that was pretty sweet... wednesday... sat at home, went to the dermo, got some wicked sweet sunblock, went to the awana carnival.  pretty fun.  then we hit up cafe mocha for the first time ever! definitely the new hang out spot.  that place is amazing!  thursday... baked cookies with dani :) and mark and kristen and shattana... but o well.  i still got to spend time with my dani! couldnt make it to eka's... sigh.  next time though...next time.  (eka- u just gotta hit me up earlier!)  k neways... friday was craziness.  i went to the awards day at school, played some soccer, gave colin his cookie...then came home for a bit.  shimmied over to doug's to pick up him, sean, and phil then drove to davison.  fun stuff.  the service was so freaking long though! and they had some weird candle lighting ceremony...  said hi to all the ppl we knew, then hung out at the stott's and the baudoux's.  drove home in the construction barrel filled road that is I-75 and got home at 1.  mom wasnt happy lol... today- went to jaime's open house, tiff's open house, and the athens graduation.  o my word that school is huge!  about 500 graduates! that took forever to hand out their diplomas! GAH! then went to red lobster with our friends, and then watched the pistons game at christians.  yeah pistons! 3-3 my friends... pistons party neone?? not at my house though... just putting that out there.  

i wish dani wasnt grounded... the week b4 i leave for a month...and she's grounded.  that royally sucks.

i have a dilemma... i'm going off to college next year, to south carolina.  that's crazy far away.  i know its going to be amazing for me, and that i'll be able to learn a lot and grow a whole bunch.  But things have started coming up that make me not want to leave home... i want to be home and make more of an impact on my friends here.  for quite some time now i've been wanting to start a bible study or a teen thing...something where ppl can get together and hangout, talk about God and His impact on their lives, and just encourage each other in the faith.  i dk, i really think it would make a huge impact on ppl. 

dani...o man.  i dk...too much stuff to write...

but then on the other hand...what if i need to go to bju so i can be better prepared for all these plans?? i really dont feel ready to start a bible study on my own.  i wish i had someone who would keep me accountable, someone to push me to do my best in college, to help me stay focused on the future and the more important things in life.  when girls come into my life, i need someone to smack me and keep me on the right path, not to get all caught up in my feelings and what i want for the moment... too much more...dont want to write it all...


no comments needed...just wanted to get that all out...

after we messed around in the parking lot lol.  that was really fun.  i love my youth group!  me and jaimie broke up...sigh... o well, now i'm free to pursue tiff :) lol jk.  she dumped me even after i scratched her eyeball! i freaking touched it!!

THEN... went and picked up dani, went to macs award ceremony, mark didnt get anything (tis a robbery year for the dongons...) then we met up with jaimie and marie and went to somerset mall!  we were acting all sweet and rich in all the snobby stores lol.  dani's not good at acting... then we hit up target and then brought dani home :(  muchos music and good times
